## Task: Add prompt chips to Canvas Build empty state

The Canvas Build empty state (when no nodes exist) currently shows only a textarea and a Build button. It needs example prompts that demonstrate what users can type.

## What to build

Add 3 clickable example prompt chips above the textarea that pre-fill it when clicked. Add a one-sentence explanation.

## Files to modify

### 1. Modify: `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/CanvasBuildPage.tsx`

In the `!hasNodes` branch (around line 331), before the textarea:

```tsx
// Add these example prompts as a constant near the top of the file
const EXAMPLE_PROMPTS = [
  'Research competitor pricing, classify by tier, draft a comparison report, notify the team on Slack',
  'Every morning, pull open tickets from Linear, summarize blockers, post to #standup',
  'When a new lead arrives, enrich from public data, score fit, route to the right account exec',
];
```

In the JSX, inside the `canvas-start` div, add before the textarea:

```tsx
<div className="canvas-compose__examples">
  <div className="canvas-compose__hint">Describe what your workflow should do</div>
  {EXAMPLE_PROMPTS.map((prompt, i) => (
    <button
      key={i}
      className="canvas-compose__chip"
      onClick={() => dispatch({ type: 'SET_PROSE', prose: prompt })}
    >
      {prompt.length > 60 ? prompt.slice(0, 57) + '...' : prompt}
    </button>
  ))}
</div>
```

