- Do NOT add template previews or chain miniatures — just text chips

## Task: Unify catalog items into the node popout, kill CanvasReel

The debate established that the popout's 7-item CanvasReel and the Action dock's 21-item catalog are redundant. Unify them: the popout shows all node-action catalog items (not edge gates), and the CanvasReel component is deleted.

## What to build

### 1. Modify: `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/CanvasPopout.tsx`

Replace the CanvasReel-based action picker with an inline catalog grid showing node-action items from catalog.ts.

- Remove the import of `CanvasReel` and `ReelOption`
- Remove the `ACTION_ARCHETYPES` constant (the 7 hardcoded options)
- Import `CATALOG, catalogByFamily, FAMILY_LABELS` from `./catalog` and `CatalogFamily` type
- Filter catalog to node-action items: `const nodeItems = CATALOG.filter(c => c.dropKind === 'node' && c.status === 'ready')`
- Add `familyFilter` state (useState<CatalogFamily | null>(null))
- Render family filter tabs (Trigger, Gather, Think, Act — NOT Control, those are edge gates)
- Render filtered items as a compact grid of clickable cards with glyph icon + label
- When a card is clicked, call `onSelect(node.id, item.actionValue!)` directly
- Keep the contextual question (`questionFor`) and dock hint (`dockHint`) logic
- Keep the Apply button for confirming selection, or auto-apply on click (simpler — auto-apply)
- Keep click-outside and Escape close behavior
- Preserve keyboard navigation: arrow keys move between catalog items

The popout should go from 139 lines to approximately 150-170 lines. It renders a compact 2-column grid of catalog items, not a scrollable reel.

