## Task: Add readiness checklist with Fix buttons to Release tray

The Release tray currently shows status passively (readiness dots, blocker list, dispatch button). Transform it into a guided checklist where each item is clickable and navigates to the problem.

## What to build

### 1. Modify: `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/canvasBuildPresenter.ts`

Extend the `ReleaseStatus` interface to include a checklist:

```typescript
export interface ReadinessItem {
  label: string;
  passed: boolean;
  nodeId?: string;  // which node to navigate to
  dock?: 'action' | 'detail';  // which dock to open
  message: string;  // e.g. "3 nodes need types" or "All nodes typed"
}

export interface ReleaseStatus {
  readiness: 'ready' | 'blocked' | 'draft';
  blockers: { message: string; severity: string; nodeIds: string[] }[];
  projectedJobs: { label: string; agent: string }[];
  checklist: ReadinessItem[];  // NEW
}
```

In the `presentBuild` function, compute the checklist from existing data:

```typescript
const checklist: ReadinessItem[] = [];

// 1. All nodes typed?
const untypedNodes = nodes.filter(n => n.isOnDominantPath && (n.ringState === 'unresolved' || n.ringState === 'active-unresolved'));
checklist.push({
  label: 'All nodes typed',
  passed: untypedNodes.length === 0,
  nodeId: untypedNodes[0]?.id,
  message: untypedNodes.length === 0 ? 'All nodes have types' : `${untypedNodes.length} node${untypedNodes.length > 1 ? 's' : ''} need types`,
});

// 2. All context attached?
const incompleteNodes = nodes.filter(n => n.isOnDominantPath && n.needsBadge);
checklist.push({
  label: 'Context attached',
  passed: incompleteNodes.length === 0,
  nodeId: incompleteNodes[0]?.id,
  dock: 'detail',
  message: incompleteNodes.length === 0 ? 'All nodes have context' : `${incompleteNodes.length} node${incompleteNodes.length > 1 ? 's' : ''} need context`,
});

// 3. No blockers?
checklist.push({
  label: 'No blockers',
  passed: blockers.length === 0,
  nodeId: blockers[0]?.nodeIds?.[0],
  message: blockers.length === 0 ? 'No blockers' : `${blockers.length} blocker${blockers.length > 1 ? 's' : ''}`,
});

// 4. Jobs projected?
checklist.push({
  label: 'Jobs projected',
  passed: projectedJobs.length > 0,
  message: projectedJobs.length > 0 ? `${projectedJobs.length} jobs ready` : 'No jobs — compile first',
});
```

### 2. Modify: `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/CanvasReleaseTray.tsx`

Replace the proof-checks section (lines 107-119) with the new checklist:

- Add new props: `onSelectNode?: (nodeId: string) => void`, `onOpenDock?: (dock: string) => void`
- Render `release.checklist` items instead of the hardcoded proof dots
- Each item shows a green dot (passed) or amber dot (not passed) + message
- Failed items with a `nodeId` get a "Fix" button that calls `onSelectNode(item.nodeId)` and optionally `onOpenDock(item.dock)`
- The Fix button should use the existing `canvas-dock-form__btn--small` CSS class

### 3. Modify: `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/CanvasBuildPage.tsx`

Pass the new props to CanvasReleaseTray:

```tsx
<CanvasReleaseTray
  release={viewModel.release}
  payload={payload}
  workflowId={workflowId}
  onClose={() => dispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_RELEASE' })}
  onSelectNode={(nodeId) => {
    dispatch({ type: 'SELECT_NODE', nodeId });
    // The popout will open automatically via SELECT_NODE
  }}
  onOpenDock={(dock) => {
    dispatch({ type: 'OPEN_DOCK', dock: dock as any });
  }}
/>
```

## Key constraints
- The presenter changes are pure computation from existing data — no new API calls needed
- The checklist items should be computed, not hardcoded — they derive from the same data the release status already uses
- Keep the existing projected jobs list and dispatch button — the checklist replaces only the proof-checks section
- ~30 lines added to presenter, ~20 lines changed in CanvasReleaseTray, ~5 lines in CanvasBuildPage
- Do NOT turn this into a wizard or multi-step flow. It's a flat checklist with Fix links.
